1
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:33,000
"Bittersweet Love"

2
00:01:33,500 --> 00:01:38,000
(Episode 6)

3
00:02:37,541 --> 00:02:38,541
Bro, you're back.

4
00:02:44,333 --> 00:02:45,333
So much stuff!

5
00:02:45,500 --> 00:02:47,140
You should've called me down to get them.

6
00:02:47,541 --> 00:02:48,541
It's not much.

7
00:02:56,875 --> 00:02:57,375
Bro.

8
00:02:57,708 --> 00:02:59,500
Your phone's still inside the bag.

9
00:03:01,500 --> 00:03:02,500
The case is cracked.

10
00:03:03,333 --> 00:03:04,333
Toss it.

11
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:05,583
Only the case is damaged.

12
00:03:05,833 --> 00:03:07,041
The rest is all good.

13
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:09,958
Not worth the trouble to fix it.

14
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:13,541
It's a shame to toss it when it's fixable.

15
00:03:14,458 --> 00:03:15,791
Take it if you'd like.

16
00:03:16,458 --> 00:03:17,583
Fix it yourself then.

17
00:03:17,916 --> 00:03:18,916
You're giving it to me?

18
00:03:19,666 --> 00:03:20,666
It's broken anyway.

19
00:03:21,166 --> 00:03:22,566
If you don't want it, just toss it.

20
00:03:22,875 --> 00:03:24,115
I'll take it!

21
00:03:46,791 --> 00:03:47,791
Bro.

22
00:03:48,250 --> 00:03:49,625
I see a pimple on your face.

23
00:03:50,458 --> 00:03:52,166
Go easy on the blistered peppers.

24
00:03:54,875 --> 00:03:55,875
Pimple?

25
00:03:57,333 --> 00:03:58,333
Where?

26
00:03:59,541 --> 00:04:00,541
Right here.

27
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:06,666
Where?

28
00:04:07,125 --> 00:04:08,125
Here.

29
00:04:25,166 --> 00:04:26,166
Eat.

30
00:04:28,041 --> 00:04:29,041
Eat.

31
00:04:30,375 --> 00:04:31,375
Eat.

32
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:32,500
What?

33
00:04:33,666 --> 00:04:34,666
Time to eat.

34
00:05:07,666 --> 00:05:08,666
Stay over tonight.

35
00:05:20,666 --> 00:05:22,416
Hold on, I'll do the dishes first.

36
00:05:25,083 --> 00:05:26,125
I'll do the dishes first.

37
00:05:30,958 --> 00:05:32,541
Let me take a shower first.

38
00:05:40,083 --> 00:05:41,166
You can wait.

39
00:05:41,791 --> 00:05:42,791
Can he wait?

40
00:06:07,666 --> 00:06:09,375
I bought you so many briefs.

41
00:06:11,666 --> 00:06:13,250
Why are you still wearing boxers?

42
00:06:15,666 --> 00:06:17,666
They're not...
they're not comfortable to wear.

43
00:06:19,250 --> 00:06:20,250
Is that so?

44
00:06:31,375 --> 00:06:32,666
Is this more comfortable?

45
00:06:59,333 --> 00:07:00,833
I'd better go take a shower.

46
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,000
Fanfan.

47
00:07:51,291 --> 00:07:52,708
I've already let Lüxin know.

48
00:07:53,208 --> 00:07:54,208
Don't worry.

49
00:09:13,333 --> 00:09:14,541
Bro, I'm heading back now.

50
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:18,500
Stay.

51
00:09:36,583 --> 00:09:37,083
Let's go.

52
00:09:37,375 --> 00:09:38,655
I'll take you to fix your phone.

53
00:09:51,833 --> 00:09:52,291
Bro.

54
00:09:52,750 --> 00:09:53,875
This key...

55
00:09:55,958 --> 00:09:57,291
It's for you, so just take it.

56
00:10:06,541 --> 00:10:07,541
It looks really nice.

57
00:10:09,250 --> 00:10:10,250
The scarf?

58
00:10:12,500 --> 00:10:15,000
The scarf is really warm too.

59
00:10:20,708 --> 00:10:21,708
Let's go.

60
00:10:21,833 --> 00:10:22,833
Mm.

61
00:10:29,666 --> 00:10:30,083
Hello.

62
00:10:30,291 --> 00:10:31,291
How can I help you?

63
00:10:31,666 --> 00:10:32,684
I need to stop by the department first.

64
00:10:32,708 --> 00:10:33,767
Catch up later if there's anything.

65
00:10:33,791 --> 00:10:34,791
Mm.

66
00:10:37,250 --> 00:10:37,708
Excuse me.

67
00:10:38,041 --> 00:10:39,250
I've got a phone here.

68
00:10:39,291 --> 00:10:40,291
Can you fix it?

69
00:10:43,208 --> 00:10:43,666
It can't be fixed.

70
00:10:43,667 --> 00:10:44,934
The whole part needs to be replaced.

71
00:10:44,958 --> 00:10:45,666
We need to order the part.

72
00:10:45,667 --> 00:10:46,750
It'll be a few days.

73
00:10:47,541 --> 00:10:48,291
That's fine.

74
00:10:48,541 --> 00:10:49,833
I'll pick it up in a few days.

75
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:52,208
Okay, fifty yuan deposit first.

76
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:54,583
Here you go.

77
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,000
Hang on to this.

78
00:10:56,541 --> 00:10:57,541
Thanks.

79
00:11:02,041 --> 00:11:03,041
Brother.

80
00:11:07,541 --> 00:11:09,500
Wow, you still know I prefer this blend.

81
00:11:20,166 --> 00:11:21,166
What are you doing?

82
00:11:21,791 --> 00:11:22,791
No need?

83
00:11:23,250 --> 00:11:23,791
Forget it, then.

84
00:11:23,875 --> 00:11:24,875
Hey.

85
00:11:26,875 --> 00:11:28,166
Once you write this check,

86
00:11:28,791 --> 00:11:30,791
I won't see you for ages.

87
00:11:36,250 --> 00:11:38,000
All you do is sleep at home

88
00:11:38,541 --> 00:11:40,666
or fool around with your friends.

89
00:11:42,125 --> 00:11:43,291
As your elder brother,

90
00:11:43,958 --> 00:11:44,875
I really don't know

91
00:11:44,876 --> 00:11:46,250
how to get along with you.

92
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:48,875
Why don't you use this check

93
00:11:49,333 --> 00:11:50,373
to start a small business?

94
00:11:50,791 --> 00:11:53,482
And see how the world
out there has changed.

95
00:11:56,041 --> 00:11:57,833
This isn't just about having fun.

96
00:11:58,958 --> 00:12:01,625
I mean the whole way the world
operates has shifted.

97
00:12:02,458 --> 00:12:03,698
Once you broaden your horizons,

98
00:12:04,166 --> 00:12:06,041
we'll have plenty more to chat about.

99
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:07,500
Don't you think?

100
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:11,000
There's one more thing.

101
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:15,041
The Lus will be here in a few days.

102
00:12:15,375 --> 00:12:16,749
Act as their daughter-in-law,

103
00:12:16,750 --> 00:12:17,916
and treat them well.

104
00:12:21,166 --> 00:12:22,250
Ow, ow, Brother.

105
00:12:22,500 --> 00:12:23,541
Fine, I'll do it.

106
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:32,666
So what should we go eat later?

107
00:12:33,083 --> 00:12:34,958
I know a great Japanese place nearby.

108
00:12:35,708 --> 00:12:37,375
Are you off to find Lu Xiaofan again?

109
00:12:38,375 --> 00:12:40,916
You care more about the fake
brother-in-law than your sister.

110
00:12:41,375 --> 00:12:43,015
Just remember to do what you promised me.

111
00:12:43,083 --> 00:12:44,083
Hey!

112
00:12:58,541 --> 00:12:59,541
Mom.

113
00:13:00,083 --> 00:13:01,523
Weiwei and I are in a fake marriage.

114
00:13:02,375 --> 00:13:03,458
Sam is my real friend.

115
00:13:04,916 --> 00:13:05,916
Friend?

116
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:08,000
Friend.

117
00:13:08,208 --> 00:13:09,208
Lover.

118
00:13:09,708 --> 00:13:10,708
Mom.

119
00:13:10,833 --> 00:13:13,499
Gay people can click on every level.

120
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:15,958
Yet making a life
together is incredibly hard.

121
00:13:16,375 --> 00:13:18,540
So Sam and I really treasure each other.

122
00:13:18,541 --> 00:13:19,832
Is it really that moving?

123
00:13:19,833 --> 00:13:20,041
Look.

124
00:13:20,042 --> 00:13:21,291
Among our friends,

125
00:13:21,458 --> 00:13:22,767
these so-called normal couples...

126
00:13:22,791 --> 00:13:24,916
They're all pitiful, really.

127
00:13:29,041 --> 00:13:30,458
Especially that white guy.

128
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:33,666
He never belonged in
their world to begin with.

129
00:13:34,958 --> 00:13:36,791
The thing between Weitong and Weiwei.

130
00:13:37,250 --> 00:13:38,250
For him,

131
00:13:38,833 --> 00:13:40,166
he'd be heartbroken too.

132
00:13:43,875 --> 00:13:44,875
Really?

133
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:48,000
Bro.

134
00:13:48,375 --> 00:13:49,375
Don't you think so?

135
00:13:49,791 --> 00:13:52,833
Weitong betrayed Simon, actually.

136
00:13:54,875 --> 00:13:55,875
From now on,

137
00:13:56,166 --> 00:13:57,625
he'll just be

138
00:13:58,250 --> 00:13:59,875
an outsider in this family.

139
00:14:09,166 --> 00:14:10,166
Fanfan.

140
00:14:11,958 --> 00:14:13,833
You really don't need
to read so much into it.

141
00:14:23,166 --> 00:14:24,166
Are you hungry?

142
00:14:24,250 --> 00:14:25,750
I'll take you out for a bite.

143
00:14:29,791 --> 00:14:31,208
Let's eat something else, then.

144
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:53,166
Mom and them are coming tomorrow.

145
00:15:15,333 --> 00:15:16,708
I went and bought some things.

146
00:15:18,333 --> 00:15:19,333
These two

147
00:15:19,375 --> 00:15:20,375
are for Mr. Lu.

148
00:15:21,333 --> 00:15:22,541
These two are for Mrs. Lu.

149
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,875
These pajamas are also for Mrs. Lu.

150
00:15:26,125 --> 00:15:27,965
The fabric feels really
nice against the skin.

151
00:15:28,750 --> 00:15:30,166
This jacket is for the little one.

152
00:15:30,666 --> 00:15:32,500
Young people should dress more stylishly.

153
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:34,750
This bracelet is for her too.

154
00:15:38,333 --> 00:15:39,333
Bro.

155
00:15:39,458 --> 00:15:40,458
She's still a kid.

156
00:15:40,750 --> 00:15:42,250
She doesn't need a pricey bracelet.

157
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:45,708
Young folks love this kind of thing now.

158
00:15:47,916 --> 00:15:49,596
I have things to do, so I'll be going now.

159
00:15:49,666 --> 00:15:50,875
When they come,

160
00:15:51,041 --> 00:15:52,681
I might not have time to look after them.

161
00:15:52,750 --> 00:15:53,950
Don't feel pressured about it.

162
00:15:55,541 --> 00:15:56,791
Ah, thank you, bro.

163
00:16:27,208 --> 00:16:28,208
Bro.

164
00:16:28,250 --> 00:16:30,833
You forgot your scarf.

165
00:16:31,250 --> 00:16:32,250
That's not mine.

166
00:16:33,666 --> 00:16:37,250
I noticed you had a similar one last time.

167
00:16:40,291 --> 00:16:41,791
Oh you, you.

168
00:17:09,791 --> 00:17:10,291
Hello?

169
00:17:10,666 --> 00:17:11,666
Bro.

170
00:17:11,958 --> 00:17:12,958
What's wrong?

171
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:16,000
I'm still a little worried.

172
00:17:16,333 --> 00:17:17,893
Lüxin didn't want to come this morning.

173
00:17:18,291 --> 00:17:19,333
I'm afraid...

174
00:17:19,583 --> 00:17:20,583
Fanfan.

175
00:17:20,708 --> 00:17:21,726
It's too noisy over there.

176
00:17:21,750 --> 00:17:22,375
Can you hear me?
I really can't hear you.

177
00:17:23,291 --> 00:17:23,875
Hello?

178
00:17:24,166 --> 00:17:25,166
Bro.

179
00:17:25,500 --> 00:17:26,875
As long as you get them safe.

180
00:17:27,166 --> 00:17:28,246
Everything's been arranged.

181
00:17:31,250 --> 00:17:32,250
Okay.

182
00:17:45,250 --> 00:17:45,708
Dad.

183
00:17:45,958 --> 00:17:47,416
Why did you bring so much stuff?

184
00:17:47,750 --> 00:17:48,750
Ask your mother.

185
00:17:49,541 --> 00:17:51,875
Can you show up
empty-handed on your first visit?

186
00:17:52,583 --> 00:17:54,124
Just store-bought stuff,

187
00:17:54,125 --> 00:17:55,166
nothing special.

188
00:17:55,375 --> 00:17:57,215
The Beis are loaded,
they can afford anything.

189
00:17:57,291 --> 00:17:57,958
If you're gonna bring something,

190
00:17:58,041 --> 00:17:59,583
get what money can't buy.

191
00:18:00,541 --> 00:18:01,041
Mom.

192
00:18:01,333 --> 00:18:02,500
Why are your eyes all red?

193
00:18:02,958 --> 00:18:04,791
She knew she'd take the train,

194
00:18:05,375 --> 00:18:06,375
and was so excited

195
00:18:06,500 --> 00:18:08,041
she couldn't sleep all night.

196
00:18:08,125 --> 00:18:08,958
You old fool.

197
00:18:08,959 --> 00:18:10,249
It's all because of that train.

198
00:18:10,250 --> 00:18:11,875
Rocking and shaking.

199
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:13,333
So many people sleeping together.

200
00:18:13,916 --> 00:18:15,333
How was I supposed to sleep?

201
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:16,665
I like sleeper trains best.

202
00:18:16,666 --> 00:18:18,333
Feels like sleeping in a cradle.

203
00:18:18,500 --> 00:18:19,291
Rocking and shaking.
I fall asleep right away.

204
00:18:20,916 --> 00:18:21,833
You silly girl.

205
00:18:21,916 --> 00:18:23,434
You're all grown up,
still sleeping in a cradle?

206
00:18:23,458 --> 00:18:24,978
Look at you, so pleased with yourself.

207
00:18:43,166 --> 00:18:44,458
Why aren't we staying at home?

208
00:18:45,083 --> 00:18:46,083
The house is too crowded.

209
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,280
I didn't want you to lose sleep.

210
00:18:49,458 --> 00:18:50,458
This is a nice hotel.

211
00:18:50,541 --> 00:18:51,661
Lüxin arranged it specially.

212
00:18:53,291 --> 00:18:54,767
It's a long trip for you to get to Yunjing.

213
00:18:54,791 --> 00:18:55,915
You need a good night's sleep

214
00:18:55,916 --> 00:18:57,666
to have energy to explore tomorrow.

215
00:18:59,875 --> 00:19:00,708
Silly child.

216
00:19:00,833 --> 00:19:02,750
We're used to hard beds.

217
00:19:03,041 --> 00:19:04,291
Any floor works for us.

218
00:19:05,333 --> 00:19:06,125
Besides,

219
00:19:06,166 --> 00:19:08,166
your money is practically ours anyway.

220
00:19:08,333 --> 00:19:10,293
It's a total waste of
money. Not worth it at all.

221
00:19:11,125 --> 00:19:11,625
Wu,

222
00:19:12,083 --> 00:19:14,243
let's head over to the
Beis' place first to see Lvxin.

223
00:19:16,833 --> 00:19:17,833
Let's go, Wu.

224
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:28,416
Fanfan, it's so beautiful.

225
00:19:28,708 --> 00:19:29,708
Aunt Lin.

226
00:19:29,833 --> 00:19:30,500
My parents are here.

227
00:19:30,541 --> 00:19:31,541
Fanfan's mom.

228
00:19:31,583 --> 00:19:32,583
Little Fanfan's here.

229
00:19:33,250 --> 00:19:33,958
Mom.

230
00:19:34,083 --> 00:19:35,166
Look at their yard.

231
00:19:35,250 --> 00:19:36,374
It's just like our pond,

232
00:19:36,375 --> 00:19:37,083
overgrown with weeds.

233
00:19:37,084 --> 00:19:38,404
Don't talk nonsense, silly child.

234
00:19:38,500 --> 00:19:40,300
As expected, the whole
family has no manners.

235
00:19:41,041 --> 00:19:42,665
Nice, very nice.

236
00:19:42,666 --> 00:19:44,333
Who are you? Don't run about!

237
00:19:45,083 --> 00:19:46,583
Aunt Lin just cleaned up.

238
00:19:48,708 --> 00:19:50,125
The house was just tidied.

239
00:19:52,250 --> 00:19:53,750
No manners at all!

240
00:19:55,125 --> 00:19:56,125
Get down, you silly girl.

241
00:19:56,166 --> 00:19:57,499
No running around others' homes!

242
00:19:57,500 --> 00:19:58,666
Other people's?

243
00:19:58,708 --> 00:19:59,788
This is my brother's place!

244
00:20:02,375 --> 00:20:03,665
She's just a curious child.

245
00:20:03,666 --> 00:20:04,666
Let her have a look.

246
00:20:04,916 --> 00:20:06,500
Lüxin is just a kid.

247
00:20:06,625 --> 00:20:08,385
She won't hold it
against her little sister.

248
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:10,333
Lüxin,

249
00:20:10,791 --> 00:20:11,875
My parents are here.

250
00:20:14,166 --> 00:20:15,458
Dad, Mom.

251
00:20:17,333 --> 00:20:18,333
Dear child,

252
00:20:18,375 --> 00:20:20,291
Have you felt better these years?

253
00:20:24,333 --> 00:20:25,333
It's alright.

254
00:20:26,333 --> 00:20:27,333
Xiaofan.

255
00:20:27,375 --> 00:20:28,895
Did you take Mom and Dad to the hotel?

256
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:31,250
I booked that hotel specially.

257
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:32,780
It's close to the tourist spots.

258
00:20:34,166 --> 00:20:35,374
We won't stay in a hotel.

259
00:20:35,375 --> 00:20:37,541
We can just sleep on the floor at home.

260
00:20:37,708 --> 00:20:38,708
Don't waste the money.

261
00:20:38,875 --> 00:20:40,041
How would that even work?

262
00:20:43,125 --> 00:20:44,125
How about this?

263
00:20:44,250 --> 00:20:45,708
I'll call my bro,

264
00:20:46,125 --> 00:20:48,000
and let my parents use his room.

265
00:20:48,375 --> 00:20:49,208
Would that be alright?
No.

266
00:20:52,458 --> 00:20:53,000
Brother.

267
00:20:53,125 --> 00:20:55,231
Why isn't any of your
stuff in Lüxin's room?

268
00:20:57,916 --> 00:20:58,583
Fanfan.

269
00:20:58,833 --> 00:20:59,953
Where do you sleep at night?

270
00:21:01,958 --> 00:21:02,958
I sleep upstairs.

271
00:21:03,083 --> 00:21:04,643
I've got plenty of work to do at night.

272
00:21:04,791 --> 00:21:05,991
I don't want to disturb Lüxin.

273
00:21:10,666 --> 00:21:11,957
How can a married couple

274
00:21:11,958 --> 00:21:13,291
sleep in separate rooms?

275
00:21:13,541 --> 00:21:14,625
That's not proper.

276
00:21:15,166 --> 00:21:16,916
Your mom and I were just saying at home.

277
00:21:17,250 --> 00:21:18,583
It's been five years,

278
00:21:18,750 --> 00:21:20,125
and you still don't have a kid.

279
00:21:20,541 --> 00:21:21,541
Alright, alright.

280
00:21:21,791 --> 00:21:22,833
They're adults now.

281
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:24,333
They know what to do.

282
00:21:25,333 --> 00:21:26,916
Besides, work is important too.

283
00:21:27,791 --> 00:21:28,791
Well then.

284
00:21:28,833 --> 00:21:30,125
We'll stay in Fanfan's room.

285
00:21:30,291 --> 00:21:32,041
Fanfan, you move back to Lüxin's room.

286
00:21:32,333 --> 00:21:33,875
Put work aside for these few days.

287
00:21:34,041 --> 00:21:35,541
Don't keep your wife from resting.

288
00:21:38,125 --> 00:21:39,083
I almost forgot.

289
00:21:39,084 --> 00:21:40,332
Lunch is almost ready.

290
00:21:40,333 --> 00:21:41,415
Let's head to the living room.

291
00:21:41,416 --> 00:21:43,576
You've traveled so far, and
not even a sip of tea yet.

292
00:21:49,291 --> 00:21:50,291
Mom, let's go.

293
00:22:01,041 --> 00:22:02,041
I'm full, honestly.

294
00:22:02,083 --> 00:22:03,291
I can't take any more.

295
00:22:03,500 --> 00:22:04,541
Told you not to overeat.

296
00:22:04,791 --> 00:22:05,791
We brought you all the way here.

297
00:22:05,792 --> 00:22:07,512
How would we let you eat poorly these days?

298
00:22:09,500 --> 00:22:11,500
A servant who serves a
respectable household.

299
00:22:11,958 --> 00:22:13,875
Her cooking is simply superb.

300
00:22:14,125 --> 00:22:15,457
Aunt Lin is our family helper.

301
00:22:15,458 --> 00:22:16,976
She's been with us since I was little.

302
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:18,000
Don't call her a servant.

303
00:22:23,125 --> 00:22:24,000
Look at my big mouth.

304
00:22:24,001 --> 00:22:25,125
That's exactly what I meant.

305
00:22:28,291 --> 00:22:30,131
Mom, Dad, finish up
and head upstairs to rest.

306
00:22:30,500 --> 00:22:31,500
I have to go.

307
00:22:31,541 --> 00:22:32,791
The elders haven't left,

308
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:34,291
but you're heading out first.

309
00:22:35,250 --> 00:22:37,010
Napping is a tradition
in the Bei household.

310
00:22:37,291 --> 00:22:38,583
Dad, Mom.

311
00:22:38,750 --> 00:22:40,333
You can rest in my room in a bit.

312
00:22:41,166 --> 00:22:42,446
I've got errands to run outside.

313
00:22:46,333 --> 00:22:46,833
Brother.

314
00:22:47,041 --> 00:22:48,750
Aren't we going to look around Yunjing?

315
00:22:49,416 --> 00:22:50,416
Hello.

316
00:22:51,833 --> 00:22:52,833
Hello.

317
00:22:54,458 --> 00:22:55,658
I'm here to pick up the phone.

318
00:22:57,166 --> 00:22:58,166
The phone?

319
00:22:58,458 --> 00:22:59,041
Brother.

320
00:22:59,064 --> 00:23:00,481
You've got a phone now?

321
00:23:00,833 --> 00:23:02,250
It's Lüqing's used phone.

322
00:23:02,659 --> 00:23:03,659
I got it fixed up.

323
00:23:04,416 --> 00:23:05,642
Your phone is with the manager.

324
00:23:05,666 --> 00:23:06,946
I'll go get the manager for you.

325
00:23:10,916 --> 00:23:11,916
Look at that...

326
00:23:12,375 --> 00:23:13,541
It's our inexperience.

327
00:23:13,666 --> 00:23:15,026
Sorry to keep you waiting so long.

328
00:23:26,166 --> 00:23:27,166
It's as good as new!

329
00:23:27,333 --> 00:23:28,832
Just swap the case, and it's good as new.

330
00:23:28,833 --> 00:23:29,873
Are you satisfied with it?

331
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:32,708
Perfect! I'm totally satisfied.
How much?

332
00:23:33,666 --> 00:23:34,583
Think nothing of it.

333
00:23:34,584 --> 00:23:35,664
We can't accept your money.

334
00:23:37,125 --> 00:23:38,457
It's still covered by warranty.

335
00:23:38,458 --> 00:23:39,458
No payment needed.

336
00:23:40,541 --> 00:23:41,541
Well, thank you then.

337
00:23:42,833 --> 00:23:43,833
Let's go, little one.

338
00:23:50,500 --> 00:23:52,250
Thought it was some girl,

339
00:23:52,416 --> 00:23:54,250
all that cash and trouble.

340
00:23:54,541 --> 00:23:56,083
He ordered two imported phones.

341
00:23:56,458 --> 00:23:58,208
Stomped one to give to him.

342
00:23:58,500 --> 00:24:00,750
Then replaced it with a new one.

343
00:24:01,958 --> 00:24:03,290
Turns out it's a young man.

344
00:24:03,291 --> 00:24:04,332
Mind your job.

345
00:24:04,333 --> 00:24:05,333
Don't gossip.

346
00:24:09,333 --> 00:24:10,333
Brother.

347
00:24:10,375 --> 00:24:11,615
Didn't you say you had no time?

348
00:24:11,833 --> 00:24:13,393
I had to come anyway, even if I'm busy.

349
00:24:13,541 --> 00:24:16,333
I don't trust you to handle this.

350
00:24:16,583 --> 00:24:18,309
It's our parents' first
time visiting Yunjing.

351
00:24:18,333 --> 00:24:20,458
Fanfan is much more capable now.

352
00:24:20,916 --> 00:24:22,165
After all, he's married now.

353
00:24:22,166 --> 00:24:23,446
He's far more mature and steady.

354
00:24:24,291 --> 00:24:24,708
Mom.

355
00:24:25,125 --> 00:24:26,291
I was just saying,

356
00:24:26,750 --> 00:24:28,541
the most developed countries

357
00:24:28,916 --> 00:24:30,196
are all focusing on finance now.

358
00:24:30,333 --> 00:24:32,458
Money makes money fastest.

359
00:24:33,166 --> 00:24:34,583
It's all too superficial.

360
00:24:34,750 --> 00:24:35,750
Insubstantial?

361
00:24:36,250 --> 00:24:38,041
We have a client at our office.

362
00:24:38,750 --> 00:24:41,041
His relative's only a
receptionist at the exchange,

363
00:24:42,125 --> 00:24:43,333
yet he got a tip.

364
00:24:43,458 --> 00:24:44,458
In just one week.

365
00:24:45,166 --> 00:24:46,684
Mom and Dad, guess how much they earned?

366
00:24:46,708 --> 00:24:47,708
How much?

367
00:24:50,291 --> 00:24:50,750
Thirty thousand yuan.
How much?!

368
00:24:51,916 --> 00:24:52,916
Thirty thousand yuan.

369
00:24:53,333 --> 00:24:53,916
Fanfan.

370
00:24:54,333 --> 00:24:55,666
Is what your brother said true?

371
00:24:56,166 --> 00:24:57,333
Mom, Dad.

372
00:24:57,791 --> 00:24:59,041
Ignore his nonsense.

373
00:25:00,833 --> 00:25:02,250
Just a doorman.

374
00:25:02,500 --> 00:25:04,249
How could his intel

375
00:25:04,250 --> 00:25:05,250
compare to Mr. Bei's?

376
00:25:05,750 --> 00:25:06,916
So much?

377
00:25:08,166 --> 00:25:10,125
Trust your son.

378
00:25:10,333 --> 00:25:13,833
I've got the smarts, just no shot.

379
00:25:17,708 --> 00:25:20,666
The eldest brother is indeed
smarter than the second.

380
00:25:21,875 --> 00:25:22,958
He's the eldest.

381
00:25:23,250 --> 00:25:24,770
It's no big deal that he's doing well.

382
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:25,583
Besides,

383
00:25:25,750 --> 00:25:26,666
if not for Xiaofan,

384
00:25:26,667 --> 00:25:27,987
he'd never have made it this far.

385
00:25:28,083 --> 00:25:29,541
Mom, stop talking about this.

386
00:25:30,125 --> 00:25:31,749
Fanfan spends all his time with the Beis,

387
00:25:31,750 --> 00:25:33,833
but he's still just a small supply clerk.

388
00:25:36,083 --> 00:25:37,083
Lüxin.

389
00:25:37,166 --> 00:25:38,166
Long time no see.

390
00:25:39,166 --> 00:25:41,791
Wow, Lüxin's so beautiful.

391
00:25:42,166 --> 00:25:43,500
Do you remember?

392
00:25:43,500 --> 00:25:45,125
All the neighbors were

393
00:25:45,125 --> 00:25:46,333
green with envy back then.

394
00:25:47,375 --> 00:25:48,815
Just thinking about it cheers me up.

395
00:25:48,958 --> 00:25:51,375
Envy all they want, shes my daughter-in-law.

396
00:25:51,541 --> 00:25:55,125
Xiaofan and Lüxin were perfect together.

397
00:25:55,125 --> 00:25:56,416
You didn't believe me back then…

398
00:25:58,250 --> 00:25:59,541
Securities are tricky,

399
00:26:00,375 --> 00:26:01,415
but full of opportunities.

400
00:26:01,916 --> 00:26:03,596
The key is to stick with the right people.

401
00:26:04,750 --> 00:26:07,000
When the tide rises, all boats float.

402
00:26:08,541 --> 00:26:09,833
This is our pot.

403
00:26:11,291 --> 00:26:12,833
Why let outsiders dip in first?

404
00:26:16,791 --> 00:26:17,791
Lüxin.

405
00:26:18,458 --> 00:26:19,000
Come here.

406
00:26:19,416 --> 00:26:20,958
Got a question for you, kid.

407
00:26:22,791 --> 00:26:23,791
What is it?

408
00:26:25,708 --> 00:26:27,708
Is this stock really that good?

409
00:26:29,333 --> 00:26:30,333
Yes.

410
00:26:30,458 --> 00:26:31,833
Invest smart, and you'll earn big.

411
00:26:33,500 --> 00:26:35,583
You're not sharp enough.

412
00:26:35,833 --> 00:26:38,166
That's why Uncle Bei won't take you along.

413
00:26:38,291 --> 00:26:39,291
Dad.

414
00:26:39,666 --> 00:26:41,666
Don't you know what Fanfan is made of?

415
00:26:42,125 --> 00:26:42,666
No wonder.

416
00:26:42,667 --> 00:26:43,708
Uncle Bei

417
00:26:43,750 --> 00:26:46,250
won't help his own son-in-law get rich.

418
00:26:50,541 --> 00:26:51,958
My dad doesn't trade stocks at all.

419
00:26:52,708 --> 00:26:53,908
How could he bring Xiaofan in?

420
00:26:55,666 --> 00:26:57,000
Fanfan, look.

421
00:26:57,166 --> 00:26:58,966
I'm saying, is your
family losing their cool?

422
00:26:59,000 --> 00:26:59,500
Alright, alright.

423
00:26:59,501 --> 00:27:00,666
Just mind your own business.

424
00:27:00,833 --> 00:27:02,166
Stay out of Fanfan's business.

425
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:29,666
Brother.

426
00:27:29,916 --> 00:27:31,166
It's getting late.

427
00:27:31,500 --> 00:27:32,666
You should head back now.

428
00:27:33,958 --> 00:27:35,207
I'm not going back.

429
00:27:35,208 --> 00:27:37,583
I took two days off just
to take my parents out.

430
00:27:38,666 --> 00:27:40,500
But there's no extra room here.

431
00:27:40,916 --> 00:27:43,458
Maybe you could stay at a hotel nearby.

432
00:27:45,166 --> 00:27:46,458
Isn't Lüqing staying away?

433
00:27:46,958 --> 00:27:48,158
I'll stay in his room for now.

434
00:27:48,708 --> 00:27:50,291
I've already booked a hotel.

435
00:27:54,958 --> 00:27:55,958
Pingping.

436
00:27:56,083 --> 00:27:57,791
How about staying at an inn?

437
00:27:58,916 --> 00:27:59,916
Mom.

438
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:02,000
Fine, I'll just stay out here in the yard.

439
00:28:02,750 --> 00:28:04,500
I never thought there'd be no room

440
00:28:04,708 --> 00:28:06,250
when I came to stay with my brother.

441
00:28:06,666 --> 00:28:08,165
I've got no ID, no papers.

442
00:28:08,166 --> 00:28:09,250
Where am I gonna stay?

443
00:28:09,541 --> 00:28:11,833
Strangers can't stay in his room.

444
00:28:12,166 --> 00:28:13,166
Lüxin.

445
00:28:13,291 --> 00:28:15,916
You don't want us staying here, do you?

446
00:28:16,083 --> 00:28:16,500
Dad.

447
00:28:16,875 --> 00:28:18,291
That's not what Lüxin meant.

448
00:28:19,333 --> 00:28:21,458
Lüqing's room has important files.

449
00:28:22,333 --> 00:28:23,500
Lüqing's back.

450
00:28:29,666 --> 00:28:31,500
Uncle Lu, Aunt Lu! You're here.

451
00:28:35,041 --> 00:28:36,041
Lüqing.

452
00:28:36,083 --> 00:28:37,916
You've lost so much
weight since we last met.

453
00:28:38,125 --> 00:28:39,915
Stay healthy even when you're busy.

454
00:28:39,916 --> 00:28:40,791
Brother Lüqing,

455
00:28:40,916 --> 00:28:42,125
thanks for the bracelet.

456
00:28:42,791 --> 00:28:44,291
Thanks for your concern, Aunt Lu.

457
00:28:45,583 --> 00:28:47,103
I got everyone some late-night treats.

458
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:50,000
Brother Lüqing is always
so kind to our family.

459
00:28:50,583 --> 00:28:53,666
My brother's relied on you all these years.

460
00:28:54,791 --> 00:28:56,391
Xiaofan's never been any trouble at all.

461
00:29:02,375 --> 00:29:03,541
Such big mushrooms!

462
00:29:03,666 --> 00:29:04,746
What are you talking about?

463
00:29:04,916 --> 00:29:05,916
This is abalone.

464
00:29:05,917 --> 00:29:07,237
But it looks just like mushrooms.

465
00:29:07,833 --> 00:29:08,875
Sure does.

466
00:29:11,500 --> 00:29:12,500
Dad, Mom.

467
00:29:12,833 --> 00:29:14,291
This abalone costs a fortune.

468
00:29:14,583 --> 00:29:15,790
One such abalone costs

469
00:29:15,791 --> 00:29:17,458
as much as a whole pig from our village.

470
00:29:17,916 --> 00:29:18,916
Right, Lüqing?

471
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:22,125
It's not that expensive.

472
00:29:24,541 --> 00:29:25,541
Here.

473
00:29:26,375 --> 00:29:27,375
Thank you, Mom.

474
00:29:38,291 --> 00:29:39,291
Bro.

475
00:29:40,083 --> 00:29:41,791
Brother Pingping forgot his ID,

476
00:29:42,458 --> 00:29:43,978
so he can't check into the guesthouse.

477
00:29:45,041 --> 00:29:46,041
I came back

478
00:29:46,458 --> 00:29:48,058
to bring everyone a nice little benefit.

479
00:29:48,583 --> 00:29:50,250
A friend ate out

480
00:29:50,333 --> 00:29:52,500
and scored two free hotel vouchers today.

481
00:29:53,500 --> 00:29:54,500
We locals

482
00:29:54,833 --> 00:29:55,833
don't need them anyway.

483
00:30:00,791 --> 00:30:02,291
Two free deluxe room vouchers

484
00:30:02,541 --> 00:30:04,000
from a five-star hotel.

485
00:30:05,791 --> 00:30:07,666
I didn't want them to go to wast,

486
00:30:07,958 --> 00:30:08,583
so I brought them back.

487
00:30:08,916 --> 00:30:10,309
See if anyone here would like to use them.

488
00:30:10,333 --> 00:30:11,333
I want to go!

489
00:30:14,958 --> 00:30:15,958
After dinner,

490
00:30:16,166 --> 00:30:17,583
Wu will drive you there.

491
00:30:18,833 --> 00:30:20,193
One room for Uncle Lu and Aunt Lu.

492
00:30:20,750 --> 00:30:21,750
Lu Xiaoping.

493
00:30:25,708 --> 00:30:26,708
What a shame.

494
00:30:28,083 --> 00:30:29,243
Since you don't have your ID,

495
00:30:30,041 --> 00:30:31,281
you can stay in Xiaofan's room.

496
00:30:34,375 --> 00:30:35,708
Luqing's so thoughtful,

497
00:30:36,166 --> 00:30:37,500
he's got everything sorted.

498
00:30:39,208 --> 00:30:39,916
Luqing,

499
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:41,500
you didn't pay for this, did you?

500
00:30:42,375 --> 00:30:44,041
I feel a bit bad.

501
00:30:44,166 --> 00:30:44,833
Aunt Lu,

502
00:30:45,166 --> 00:30:46,208
rest easy staying here.

503
00:30:47,833 --> 00:30:49,041
Thanks a lot, Luqing!

504
00:31:01,166 --> 00:31:01,708
Bro.

505
00:31:02,166 --> 00:31:04,333
You left your scarf here last time.

506
00:31:12,875 --> 00:31:14,500
This scarf is meant for you.

507
00:31:17,250 --> 00:31:18,250
This...

508
00:31:19,083 --> 00:31:20,291
This scarf is too expensive.

509
00:31:20,416 --> 00:31:21,416
I've got no use for it.

510
00:31:21,750 --> 00:31:22,041
You...

511
00:31:22,375 --> 00:31:23,375
You keep it then.

512
00:31:26,416 --> 00:31:28,216
Just get rid of it if
you have no need for it.

513
00:32:21,708 --> 00:32:23,250
Your phone's fixed,

514
00:32:24,541 --> 00:32:25,750
The SIM card is installed.

515
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:29,500
It's completely free for calls.

516
00:32:31,583 --> 00:32:32,583
Bro.

517
00:32:33,375 --> 00:32:34,833
The phone still looks brand new.

518
00:32:35,500 --> 00:32:36,500
How about

519
00:32:36,833 --> 00:32:38,250
you take it back and use it?

520
00:32:47,708 --> 00:32:48,708
It's fine.

521
00:32:50,833 --> 00:32:52,041
I bought a new one myself.

522
00:32:54,333 --> 00:32:55,583
You keep this one.

523
00:32:57,333 --> 00:32:58,333
From now on,

524
00:32:59,666 --> 00:33:01,186
just don't let me lose touch with you.

525
00:33:03,541 --> 00:33:04,541
You hear me?

526
00:33:17,125 --> 00:33:18,666
Are you a dog?

527
00:33:26,833 --> 00:33:27,833
Bro.

528
00:33:40,875 --> 00:33:41,875
Fanfan.

529
00:33:44,083 --> 00:33:46,291
Can we still be like we were before?

530
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:09,000
Which "before"?

531
00:34:27,348 --> 00:34:28,388
Once your parents leave...

532
00:34:30,375 --> 00:34:31,750
could you move back to stay here?
